  "description": "Core Bard Traits\n\nPrimary Ability\n\nCharisma\n\nHit Point Die\n\nD8 per Bard level\n\nSaving Throw Proficiencies\n\nDexterity and Charisma\n\nSkill Proficiencies\n\nChoose any 3 skills\n\nWeapon Proficiencies\n\nSimple weapons\n\nTool Proficiencies\n\nChoose 3 Musical Instruments\n\nArmor Training\n\nLight armor\n\nStarting Equipment\n\nChoose A or B: (A) Leather Armor, 2 Daggers, Musical Instrument of your choice, Entertainer's Pack, and [[/award 19gp]]; or (B) [[/award 90GP]]\n\n@Embed[Compendium.dnd5e.content24.JournalEntry.phbAppendixClass.JournalEntryPage.phbbrdBard000000 inline classes=\"free-rules-embed\"]\n\nBecoming a Bard \u2026\n\nAs a Level 1 Character\n\nGain all the traits in the Core Bard Traits table.\n\nGain the Bard's level 1 features, which are listed in the Bard Features table.\n\nAs a Multiclass Character\n\nGain the following traits from the Core Bard Traits table: Hit Point Die, proficiency in one skill of your choice, proficiency with one Musical Instrument of your choice, and training with Light armor.\n\nGain the Bard's level 1 features, which are listed in the Bard Features table. See the multiclassing rules in chapter 2 to determine your available spell slots.",
